{"aid": "40137044", "title": "Male hippo in Japan zoo found to be female after 7 years", "url": "https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-68884548", "domain": "bbc.co.uk", "votes": 3, "user": "vinni2", "posted_at": "2024-04-23 20:44:34", "comments": 0, "source_title": "Male hippo in Japan zoo found to be female after 7 years", "source_text": "Male hippo in Japan zoo found to be female after 7 years\n\n# Male hippo in Japan zoo found to be female after 7 years\n\n4 hours ago\n\nBy Vicky Wong,BBC News\n\nOsaka Tennoji Zoo\n\nA DNA test has confirmed that Gen-chan, thought for seven years to be a he, is\nin fact a she\n\nA zoo in Japan has confirmed that a hippopotamus thought for seven years to be\na he is, in fact, a she.\n\nA DNA test was carried out after zookeepers noticed that 12-year-old Gen-chan\ndid not display typical male hippo behaviour.\n\nGen-chan arrived in Osaka from Mexico in 2017, and customs documents at the\ntime said she was male.\n\n\"We will keep doing our best to provide comfortable environment to Gen-chan,\"\nthe zoo said.\n\nThe Osaka Tennoji Zoo confirmed the news about Gen-chan's actual sex in a post\npublished on their website last week.\n\nThe post said Gen-chan first arrived at their zoo from the Africam Safari\nanimal park in Mexico when she was five years old, and was declared as a male.\n\nThe statement said that because Gen-chan was still a calf at the time, they\ndid not question the documents.\n\nBut zookeepers got suspicious as Gen-chan got older and they could not\nvisually identify male reproductive organs.\n\nA spokeswoman for the Osaka Tennoji Zoo told AFP on Tuesday that typical male\nhippo behaviour that Gen-chan was not displaying included making courtship\ncalls to female hippos, or scattering faeces around while defecating with a\npropeller-like tail motion in order to mark territory.\n\nAccording to the Mainichi newspaper, the zoo's vice director Kiyoshi Yasufuku\nsaid: \"We recognise the importance of confirming the sex, and we want to\nensure that such mistakes will not happen again.\"\n\nThe zoo confirmed that Gen-chan will not be getting a name change.\n\n## Safari park's announces death of 'beloved' hippo\n\n## Climate change and crocodiles in a Kenyan lake\n\nAsia\n\nZoos and Zoology\n\nJapan\n\nAnimals\n\nRelated\n\n## The fate of Korea's 'first and biggest' sex festival\n\n59 mins ago\n\nAsia\n\n## India's prime minister eyeing a historic third term\n\n4 hrs ago\n\nIndia\n\n## Diabetic Delhi leader finally gets insulin jab in jail\n\n13 hrs ago\n\nIndia\n\nMore\n\n5 hrs ago\n\n## Shogun: A guide to the hit Japanese epic\n\nA quick guide as the razor-sharp, critically-acclaimed samurai epic reaches\nits finale.\n\n5 hrs ago\n\nEntertainment & Arts\n\n6 hrs ago\n\n## Two baby camels born within a week at park\n\nDouble-humped Bactrian calves, Gillie and Billie, have joined the herd at\nBridlington Animal Park.\n\n6 hrs ago\n\nHumberside\n\n7 hrs ago\n\n## Big cat park owner disliked modern medicine - trial\n\nThe owner denies causing unnecessary suffering and using the animals for\ncommercial gain without a licence.\n\n7 hrs ago\n\nBeds, Herts & Bucks\n\n14 hrs ago\n\n## Deer return to historic park three years after cull\n\nA new herd was introduced to Dyrham Park last week, with the estate closed for\nseveral days.\n\n14 hrs ago\n\n1 day ago\n\n## Deforestation pushes animals to eat virus-laden bat poo\n\nThe creatures shed light on how new viruses might spread from animals to\nhumans, researchers say.\n\n1 day ago\n\nAfrica\n\nCopyright 2024 BBC. All rights reserved. The BBC is not responsible for the\ncontent of external sites. Read about our approach to external linking.\n\n## Let us know you agree to cookies\n\nWe use cookies to give you the best online experience.\n\nPlease let us know if you agree to all of these cookies.\n\n  * No, take me to settings\n\n", "frontpage": false}
